content: Great app. Now works perfectly. Thank you for fixing the issue with external links
Excellent
Great info on bugs and drugs
Pragmatic, accurate, funny. Like any good ID app should be!
I cannot scroll the tables horizontally, I know some of my friends had the same problem, so I know it's not because of my phone. What can I do, is there another way of having access to them? Thanks.
Exceptional Resource for inpatient Medicine.

Been using this online or as an app for 11 years. It remains unparalleled. Absolutely the best ID reference out there, and I've tried them all. Bonus humor is greatly appreciated as well. Dr. Crislip has touched and benefitted many lives.
Best infectious diseases app

A sincere thank you to Dr. Crislip for creating this amazing resource! Has been invaluable through medicine residency and now pulmccm fellowship. Quite often dispels various mythology and dogma encountered in medicine and ID.

Please provide an option to download a complete copy for use offline like the previous versions as there will be times when an internet connection is not available.  I cannot scroll the screen horizontally so the rightmost portions of long tables cant be viewed.
Easy to use
This app keeps me sane as a first year resident. I'm basically in love.
Evidence base humor
Useful explanations and informational humorous comments.
If only more people explained medicine so simple and so efficient. As a 5th year med student I give 5 star to this app. Please update it regularly :)
Wish there was a search option, rather than scrolling through everything, but other than that, great app!
Would get 5 stars if the app had smoother scrolling up and down the pages,  and transitioning between pages/menus
Just wanted to drop a line of thanks for some terrific content.  3 years running and still use this regularly. Sincerely, a simple EM doc trying not to make the MDX epidemic.

This app is really cool. It has good offline performance for when a data connection is not available. The information doesn't have the feel of something that was thrown together to put a price tag on either. It's written in such a way that some one who is just curious can browse through it and have a grasp of what he's talking about.   My one complaint is this,there is no printer integration. If that could be added in the future that would be awesome.
Great reso.urce on the fly
Fun to read, and informative of course

Thanks Mark. I've been following you (in a good way) 5yrs now. Great stuff. Recommended to all data minded fools that deal with disease! Esp those in their third even fourth decade stamping out not only the occasional puspocket, but other real disorders.  A global network.  Rated: 5.0.   recommend : .all who want truth. From student thru residents. And practitioners of real medicine on live humans without an agenda save assisting mankind in living well.
Love this app. I've worked with Dr. Crislip..he is a wealth of info and his humor on some crazy days is comic relief!!
First 'bug' that I went to was Vibrio. Whoever wrote that needs to focus on spelling errors and not on a personal global warming hypothesis.

I'm a microbiologist in a large regional medical center. This guide is spot-on for current treatment! It's like having a teaching ID doc available 24/7; and  Dr Crislip's sharp humor is hilarious!  Highly advise purchasing whether a student or experienced in clinical microbiology!
Mark, thanks for brining this to android. greatly appreciated. love your podcast. for anyone potentially interested in this, the price alone is worth the clinical pearls / jokes.
Great app  I really enjoy reading it
I've been listening to the podcast for years, and now as a poor Android shlup, I can finally get what all my iPhone colleagues have enjoyed... More Mark!
Completely non functional on DROID razr maxx with ICS. tapping a menu entry takes you to the phone dialer! Too bad because mark is an excellent source of information!
Thanks!
Huge quack cast fan and who couldn't use more mark. It's what the world needs.
Mark Crislip is my drug.

Im a huge fan of Mark Crislip and I was psyched to see his app out for Android. Unfortunately it doesnt stack up just yet. Im on a Galaxy Nexus and the type is just too small to read comfortably plus it crashes constantly. Hopefully the updates will fix this
Brilliant...and subscribe to the podcasts is essential!..at least 3 pearls of primary care utility in 30 minutes. Hard to get that any other way
